This plan was developed in consultation with the local fire department.  The refinery fire fighters and emergency response personnel routinely drill and train to maintain their skills in emergency response.


1.7    Planned Changes to Improve Safety


The refinery continually looks for and capitalizes on opportunities to improve safety.  This section provides several examples of safety initiatives relevant to the RMP and general employee safety.

Chevron Corporation awards various sites the Zero Is Attainable (ZIA) certificate for stellar safety performance.  In 2009, The El Segundo Refinery received this award due to operating without an employee or contractor OSHA recordable injury between January and May in 2009.   The refinery reached a total of 9 MM safe hours for the year.

